1
00:00:14,292 --> 00:00:15,750
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

2
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:20,083
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

3
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:23,833
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

4
00:00:26,042 --> 00:00:27,958
(Q / Q)

5
00:00:30,208 --> 00:00:32,042
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

6
00:00:36,917 --> 00:00:41,667
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 2)

7
00:00:43,625 --> 00:00:44,875
Here.

8
00:00:47,083 --> 00:00:50,000
This room stinks.

9
00:00:50,708 --> 00:00:51,726
Why did you bring me here?

10
00:00:51,750 --> 00:00:53,333
Didn't you ask me to find you a place?

11
00:00:53,458 --> 00:00:54,958
Don't tell me...

12
00:00:55,083 --> 00:00:56,500
You want me to live here?

13
00:00:57,250 --> 00:00:58,250
That's right.

14
00:01:07,167 --> 00:01:08,667
There's not even a bed...

15
00:01:09,917 --> 00:01:12,000
Or a blanket!

16
00:01:12,125 --> 00:01:15,333
I'm the prince of Blablalis!

17
00:01:16,125 --> 00:01:17,333
Look.

18
00:01:17,458 --> 00:01:20,083
Back in Kauncilion, I had my own bed.

19
00:01:20,208 --> 00:01:22,268
My blanket, everything...
It was all top-of-the-line.

20
00:01:22,292 --> 00:01:25,417
I'm not sleeping here.

21
00:01:28,792 --> 00:01:30,042
Do you hear me?

22
00:01:41,542 --> 00:01:42,583
"Proof"

23
00:01:43,167 --> 00:01:45,458
I don't even know if I'm doing a good job.

24
00:01:47,083 --> 00:01:50,667
Hiring a rookie like this...

25
00:01:51,125 --> 00:01:51,917
What is going on?

26
00:01:52,042 --> 00:01:53,458
I should just call the police.

27
00:01:53,583 --> 00:01:56,042
Boss, please give me a chance.

28
00:01:56,167 --> 00:01:58,333
I'm great at baking bread.

29
00:01:59,458 --> 00:02:00,167
Let go!

30
00:02:00,292 --> 00:02:01,500
Boss.

31
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:05,833
Boss...

32
00:02:05,958 --> 00:02:07,167
This is driving me crazy.

33
00:02:09,917 --> 00:02:12,500
Wooju, can you open the door?

34
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:15,292
Hyung.

35
00:02:15,792 --> 00:02:17,625
Why'd you show up without calling?

36
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:20,292
Since when do I need to call ahead?

37
00:02:21,417 --> 00:02:22,875
I was worried, so I came by.

38
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,208
But...

39
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:26,542
Looks like you've pretty
much got things in order.

40
00:02:28,083 --> 00:02:30,292
I've cleaned everything up.

41
00:02:32,292 --> 00:02:34,250
But who's this guy?

42
00:02:34,625 --> 00:02:35,667
He's a part-timer.

43
00:02:35,792 --> 00:02:37,292
A part-timer?

44
00:02:37,417 --> 00:02:39,101
He's an international
student from Thailand.

45
00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:41,059
I heard his family is
going through a tough time.

46
00:02:41,083 --> 00:02:42,443
My family isn't struggling at all.

47
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:43,250
I'm royalty.

48
00:02:43,375 --> 00:02:44,375
His family went bankrupt.

49
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:48,375
He sold his house just to come here.

50
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:52,625
And now he only has 150,000 won left.

51
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,250
But it seems like this
guy understands Korean.

52
00:02:57,375 --> 00:03:02,958
Yeah. So, what part of the Thai
countryside are you from?

53
00:03:03,083 --> 00:03:04,226
I'm not from the countryside.

54
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,958
I'm from the capital, a big city, okay?

55
00:03:06,083 --> 00:03:10,708
Alright. Please take good care of
Wooju Bakery and its owner.

56
00:03:11,875 --> 00:03:13,917
I'm Woo-hyuk.

57
00:03:23,875 --> 00:03:24,500
I'm Raon.

58
00:03:24,625 --> 00:03:27,292
Don't worry. I'm great at baking.

59
00:03:27,667 --> 00:03:28,750
That's enough.

60
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,167
Come here.

61
00:03:30,208 --> 00:03:30,917
Hyung.

62
00:03:31,042 --> 00:03:32,625
What's gotten into you today?

63
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:33,333
Just come here.

64
00:03:33,458 --> 00:03:34,833
Jeez.

65
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,167
Raon, go get yourself settled.

66
00:03:49,125 --> 00:03:50,667
Want to bake some bread?

67
00:03:50,792 --> 00:03:52,625
You're the one who broke the oven.

68
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:53,917
We can just fix it.

69
00:03:54,042 --> 00:03:58,458
You couldn't even fix
the car you came in...

70
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:14,292
Hey, the most important part is broken.

71
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:18,833
Hachi, can you give me a hand?

72
00:04:22,375 --> 00:04:24,417
(Wooju Bakery)

73
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:16,250
Boss, what are you thinking about?

74
00:05:21,417 --> 00:05:23,500
Just thinking about when I was a kid.

75
00:05:24,667 --> 00:05:25,458
Is that so?

76
00:05:25,583 --> 00:05:28,143
I thought you were upset because
the bread didn't turn out well.

77
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,708
What? I'm an amazing baker.

78
00:05:39,625 --> 00:05:40,917
Watch.

79
00:05:43,042 --> 00:05:44,684
When you're kneading dough,
you have to think happy thoughts.

80
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:46,583
Don't think about sad things...

81
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,125
Why?

82
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:51,167
Because even our fingertips...

83
00:05:51,292 --> 00:05:53,667
transfer our emotions into the dough.

84
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:57,250
When customers eat the bread,
they can feel it too.

85
00:06:03,542 --> 00:06:05,125
I...

86
00:06:08,667 --> 00:06:11,792
don't have many happy memories.

87
00:06:13,208 --> 00:06:18,292
Then try to think of one.

88
00:07:00,083 --> 00:07:03,417
Wow, you can see the whole city from here.

89
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:11,000
When I'm feeling down, I
come here with my hyung.

90
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:15,500
My parents passed away when I was five.

91
00:07:15,625 --> 00:07:21,750
So I met my hyung at an orphanage.

92
00:07:21,875 --> 00:07:23,292
That must have been tough.

93
00:07:24,208 --> 00:07:25,083
Not really.

94
00:07:25,208 --> 00:07:27,458
Thanks to my hyung, I managed.

95
00:07:27,917 --> 00:07:29,226
Besides, I had a dream back then.

96
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:30,000
What dream?

97
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:31,625
To open a bakery and be the owner.

98
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:33,333
So where did you learn to bake?

99
00:07:33,458 --> 00:07:35,333
At a baking school.

100
00:07:35,917 --> 00:07:37,667
But...

101
00:07:37,917 --> 00:07:39,809
You're trying to say my
bread tastes bad, aren't you?

102
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:43,875
It's because of long COVID.
I lost my sense of taste.

103
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:44,958
That's terrible.

104
00:07:45,083 --> 00:07:47,667
The doctor said it'll come back soon.

105
00:07:47,792 --> 00:07:49,208
Once my sense of taste returns...

106
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:51,268
I'm going to make bread
that's as delicious as my dad's.

107
00:07:51,292 --> 00:07:52,667
Your dad was a baker too?

108
00:07:52,792 --> 00:07:55,583
Yeah. You know Wooju Bakery, right?

109
00:07:55,708 --> 00:07:59,542
My parents used to run their bakery there.

110
00:07:59,667 --> 00:08:00,875
Really?

111
00:08:02,083 --> 00:08:04,125
The bread my dad made...

112
00:08:04,667 --> 00:08:07,042
was really special.

113
00:08:07,167 --> 00:08:11,500
I loved the star-shaped bread the most.

114
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:17,292
I've never tried your dad's bread...

115
00:08:17,542 --> 00:08:19,542
but I'm sure it was delicious.

116
00:08:19,667 --> 00:08:20,917
How do you know?

117
00:08:27,792 --> 00:08:32,583
Because I can feel the taste from
your memories in my hands right now.

118
00:08:40,875 --> 00:08:45,458
Hey, that's the kind of
line people use to flirt.

119
00:08:50,875 --> 00:08:52,917
What does your name, "Wooju," mean?

120
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:58,750
"Space, the universe."
My mom gave me that name.

121
00:09:00,292 --> 00:09:01,958
It's a beautiful name.

122
00:09:10,988 --> 00:09:12,738
Prince, want to try?

123
00:09:12,958 --> 00:09:15,708
I promise you, that one is so good.

124
00:09:27,208 --> 00:09:28,309
This is good enough to sell.

125
00:09:28,333 --> 00:09:30,500
Right? I told you.

126
00:09:30,684 --> 00:09:32,106
Give it here. Thanks.

127
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:22,792
Hello, everyone.

128
00:10:22,917 --> 00:10:26,792
Today, I'm at a bakery in Namyangju.

129
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:31,125
This place is called "Wooju Bakery."

130
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:35,417
First off, the staff here
has a terrible attitude.

131
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:37,893
A customer walked in, and
they didn't even look at me.

132
00:10:37,917 --> 00:10:41,250
Excuse me, can you recommend
your most popular item?

133
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:44,625
Poop and pee.

134
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:46,750
I'm a YouTuber with a million subscribers.

135
00:10:46,875 --> 00:10:49,167
I'm here to promote your
place, so I won't be paying.

136
00:10:49,292 --> 00:10:50,875
In fact, you should be paying me.

137
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,120
I'll just consider this me
doing you a favor, got it?

138
00:10:54,458 --> 00:10:55,792
No freebies.

139
00:10:55,917 --> 00:10:57,167
Pay first.

140
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,917
This looks like coffee with whipped cream.

141
00:11:12,333 --> 00:11:13,583
How could you...

142
00:11:14,167 --> 00:11:15,167
What the heck is this?

143
00:11:15,236 --> 00:11:15,778
Why?

144
00:11:15,917 --> 00:11:17,833
This isn't coke, and it's not coffee.

145
00:11:17,958 --> 00:11:20,000
And that on top doesn't
look like whipped cream.

146
00:11:20,125 --> 00:11:22,042
It kind of looks like mayonnaise.

147
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,000
What is this drink called?

148
00:11:26,958 --> 00:11:28,250
That's "Space Pee."

149
00:11:29,583 --> 00:11:32,292
Well, I'll try the bread then.

150
00:11:35,917 --> 00:11:37,542
Huh?

151
00:11:37,667 --> 00:11:38,667
This taste...

152
00:11:38,708 --> 00:11:41,500
This bread is called "I Miss You."

153
00:11:41,625 --> 00:11:42,625
This taste...

154
00:11:42,708 --> 00:11:46,542
Doesn't it make you cry
when you think of that person?

155
00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:47,875
What is this?

156
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,042
Ah, it's so spicy!

157
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:53,250
Seriously, what the heck?
Why is the bread spicy?

158
00:11:53,708 --> 00:11:56,375
Everyone, this bakery
is absolutely terrible.

159
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:58,042
What is this place even doing, huh?

160
00:11:58,167 --> 00:12:01,375
They put mayonnaise in their drinks
and wasabi in their bread!

161
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:03,917
Everyone, do not come to this place.

162
00:12:04,583 --> 00:12:06,083
Are you curious?

163
00:12:06,208 --> 00:12:08,875
Don't even be curious. Just stay away.

164
00:12:13,125 --> 00:12:16,333
Boss, wake up.

165
00:12:27,292 --> 00:12:28,958
Boss, get up.

166
00:12:32,542 --> 00:12:33,833
Boss.

167
00:12:35,708 --> 00:12:36,851
What the heck are you doing, you psycho?

168
00:12:36,875 --> 00:12:38,125
I'm not the psycho.

169
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:41,663
The boss who's still sleeping after
opening hours is the one with the problem.

170
00:12:42,917 --> 00:12:44,958
What? It's already past nine?

171
00:12:45,083 --> 00:12:46,750
Don't worry, the shop is already open.

172
00:12:46,875 --> 00:12:48,250
You said the shop is open?

173
00:12:48,375 --> 00:12:49,542
So what if it's open?

174
00:12:49,667 --> 00:12:53,042
To do business, you need bread at least.

175
00:12:53,167 --> 00:12:54,000
I've already made the bread.

176
00:12:54,125 --> 00:12:55,125
You know how to bake?

177
00:12:55,167 --> 00:12:58,000
I learned from the best
baker in the universe.

178
00:13:05,125 --> 00:13:06,125
Move.

179
00:13:08,583 --> 00:13:11,833
I'm sorry, it seems we're
having some issues today.

180
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:13,167
We're not having any issues.

181
00:13:14,208 --> 00:13:16,250
This is a cosmic level of deliciousness.

182
00:13:16,917 --> 00:13:20,583
Keep your voice down!
We're in front of a customer.

183
00:13:23,458 --> 00:13:25,058
This person doesn't count as a customer.

184
00:13:28,375 --> 00:13:30,792
This is unbelievable.

185
00:13:30,917 --> 00:13:31,750
Did you all see that?

186
00:13:31,875 --> 00:13:33,917
At least the owner has some sense.

187
00:13:34,042 --> 00:13:37,667
But the employee is completely shameless.

188
00:13:37,792 --> 00:13:39,625
Have you ever baked before?

189
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:43,250
I can use a translator,
so you can speak Thai.

190
00:13:44,292 --> 00:13:46,250
I'm not a professional baker.

191
00:13:46,375 --> 00:13:47,417
But I am a prince.

192
00:13:47,542 --> 00:13:50,022
And I grew up eating the most
delicious bread in the universe.

193
00:13:52,792 --> 00:13:54,042
Watch your attitude.

194
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:58,333
He has the nerve to call himself a prince.

195
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:02,167
But why would a prince be here?

196
00:14:03,167 --> 00:14:05,542
I ran away because I was
being forced into a marriage.

197
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:11,292
I needed some time to figure things out.

198
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:18,167
So you ran away from your fiancée?
How shameless.

199
00:14:20,958 --> 00:14:24,375
What is that? A person or a dog? (Used the rude version of "person")

200
00:14:26,042 --> 00:14:27,208
Hachi.

201
00:14:29,583 --> 00:14:31,083
What did you just say?

202
00:14:31,208 --> 00:14:32,333
Hachi.

203
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:33,875
Hachi.

204
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:40,958
What are you doing?
Ugh, you stink! Get away.

205
00:14:41,083 --> 00:14:43,458
Don't touch me! This is so annoying.

206
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:44,375
You're messing up my hair.

207
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:46,083
Don't touch me!

208
00:14:47,917 --> 00:14:50,708
Let go! I said, let go!

209
00:14:53,583 --> 00:14:55,250
Do you have any idea what you did wrong?

210
00:14:55,375 --> 00:14:57,375
You were sleeping.

211
00:14:57,917 --> 00:14:58,750
The store needs to stay open.

212
00:14:58,875 --> 00:15:00,292
We made the bread and drinks.

213
00:15:00,417 --> 00:15:01,292
Is there anything wrong with that?

214
00:15:01,417 --> 00:15:03,000
You call this bread and drinks?

215
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,434
The least you could do
is make something edible.

216
00:15:05,458 --> 00:15:07,393
A YouTuber with millions of
subscribers visited our shop.

217
00:15:07,417 --> 00:15:09,833
If word gets out that
we're a terrible bakery,

218
00:15:09,958 --> 00:15:12,393
we're finished. We'll go bankrupt.
We're seriously going to go bankrupt!

219
00:15:12,417 --> 00:15:14,417
But it's your fault for hiring us.

220
00:15:14,792 --> 00:15:16,875
So what? Did I ever
say I wanted to hire you?

221
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,333
And why did you suddenly bite me?

222
00:15:18,458 --> 00:15:20,625
What are you, a dog?
You actually are a dog!

223
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:22,167
Did you even taste that bread?

224
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:26,375
Why are you taking that crazy woman's
word for it and giving us a hard time?

225
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:28,000
Go on, try it yourself.

226
00:15:30,083 --> 00:15:32,292
What on earth are these ingredients?

227
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:34,917
Wasabi... and mayonnaise...

228
00:15:35,042 --> 00:15:36,500
I would never put wasabi in bread.

229
00:15:36,625 --> 00:15:38,425
And I wouldn't just
dump pepper in like this.

230
00:15:42,708 --> 00:15:44,167
I can tell without even tasting it.

231
00:16:10,542 --> 00:16:12,302
What's happening? Is
my sense of taste back?

232
00:16:14,708 --> 00:16:16,226
(Songcheon Chinese Cuisine)
Tell me about it.

233
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:18,417
That place is definitely gonna fail for real.

234
00:16:18,542 --> 00:16:21,167
That bakery was the absolute worst.

235
00:16:21,292 --> 00:16:24,625
Even the name "Wooju Bakery" is so lame.

236
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,792
The response to my video has been amazing.

237
00:16:26,917 --> 00:16:31,167
Oh, and the staff there?
They're a bunch of total weirdos.

238
00:16:31,292 --> 00:16:34,250
They're basically some kind of alien.

239
00:16:35,250 --> 00:16:37,500
So, when do I get the rest of my payment?

240
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:47,958
You scared me.

241
00:16:48,083 --> 00:16:50,833
What, are you interested in me?

242
00:16:50,958 --> 00:16:52,768
I'm a YouTuber with millions
of subscribers, you know.

243
00:16:52,792 --> 00:16:57,458
I'm not the kind of girl who
just meets up with any guy.

244
00:16:59,792 --> 00:17:03,625
Why are you so determined
to ruin Wooju Bakery?

245
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:05,875
I have millions of subscribers, okay?

246
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,375
Taking that place down
is a piece of cake for me.

247
00:17:10,250 --> 00:17:16,000
What makes you think
the people working there are like aliens?

248
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:22,583
What kind of normal person would make that
kind of bread and those kinds of drinks?

249
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,250
Besides, if they were human,

250
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:26,375
why would they take my beautiful fingers

251
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,000
and just bite them?

252
00:17:28,375 --> 00:17:30,708
So what are you planning to do next?

253
00:17:31,083 --> 00:17:33,375
I'm going to film a second video.

254
00:17:33,792 --> 00:17:36,833
I'll expose those aliens
for who they really are.

255
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:40,920
What do you plan to
do by dragging her here?

256
00:17:41,042 --> 00:17:44,250
The fact that Prince Kauncilion
is an alien has already been exposed.

257
00:17:44,375 --> 00:17:47,167
If we're not careful, he could
be captured by Earthlings.

258
00:17:47,292 --> 00:17:49,833
He might even end up being dissected.

259
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:53,833
If that happens, we'll
have no way to escape.

260
00:17:53,958 --> 00:17:57,208
We could be stuck here for a hundred years,
or even two hundred.

261
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:03,125
Hyung, this is incredible.

262
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:05,917
They made this. Try it.

263
00:18:10,042 --> 00:18:11,417
Well? What do you think?

264
00:18:14,333 --> 00:18:17,250
It doesn't taste like bread, right?

265
00:18:17,375 --> 00:18:18,833
Is this Thai food?

266
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:22,750
Raon, I've never tasted anything like this.
Do you have a recipe?

267
00:18:22,875 --> 00:18:24,208
This is unbelievably good.

268
00:18:25,208 --> 00:18:29,167
I have taste buds on my hands.

269
00:18:34,958 --> 00:18:36,792
You see all those ingredients over there?

270
00:18:37,292 --> 00:18:40,208
I taste with my hands
and create from there.

271
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:44,917
You can taste with your hands?

272
00:18:45,417 --> 00:18:47,292
So you just winged it without a recipe?

273
00:18:47,625 --> 00:18:50,125
Usually, food are made like that.

274
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:51,250
That's not what I meant.

275
00:18:51,292 --> 00:18:52,458
I mean it literally.

276
00:18:52,583 --> 00:18:54,792
I really do have taste buds on my hands.

277
00:18:56,042 --> 00:18:58,208
Dude, they're completely insane.

278
00:18:58,333 --> 00:19:00,393
A huge influencer with millions
of subscribers came by today.

279
00:19:00,417 --> 00:19:01,833
And they totally screwed up.

280
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:04,958
I think she was live streaming.

281
00:19:05,083 --> 00:19:07,167
She said she's never coming back.

282
00:19:07,292 --> 00:19:08,643
I guess we can forget
about having any customers...

283
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:12,333
It's okay. We'll start by turning
the neighbors into regulars.

284
00:19:12,458 --> 00:19:13,643
Then we'll slowly build
up our customer base.

285
00:19:13,667 --> 00:19:14,958
Hmm?

286
00:19:16,167 --> 00:19:17,375
I know you can do it.

287
00:19:18,875 --> 00:19:23,000
Are you two... also engaged?

288
00:19:23,250 --> 00:19:28,042
What, do we look like a couple who love each other?

289
00:19:28,708 --> 00:19:29,500
Yeah.

290
00:19:29,625 --> 00:19:32,167
We're just good friends.

291
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,583
Really close friends.

292
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:38,333
I thought you two were engaged.

293
00:19:38,458 --> 00:19:41,375
Like you were in a relationship.

294
00:19:42,958 --> 00:19:44,583
If you have feelings for each other,

295
00:19:44,958 --> 00:19:47,083
does that mean you're
dating or even engaged?

296
00:19:47,208 --> 00:19:48,208
Well, not necessarily...

297
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:49,542
Actually, I have a fiancée too.

298
00:19:49,667 --> 00:19:51,333
But we're not together because of love.

299
00:19:52,708 --> 00:19:56,042
He left his fiancée back home
and just took off.

300
00:19:56,583 --> 00:19:57,875
What was it called...

301
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:01,042
To get out of an arranged
political marriage, he said.

302
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,500
An arranged marriage?
Everyone knows about those.

303
00:20:05,625 --> 00:20:08,583
That's something only rich families do.

304
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:09,958
I...

305
00:20:12,292 --> 00:20:12,875
Prince...

306
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,167
I feel them... they're coming!

307
00:20:15,292 --> 00:20:16,583
Who's here?

308
00:20:30,208 --> 00:20:32,625
Princess, come in.

309
00:21:05,208 --> 00:21:07,667
I thought you'd fled to
the ends of the universe.

310
00:21:07,792 --> 00:21:09,333
But you only made it to Earth?

311
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,917
Your Highness, you've had a long journey.

312
00:21:18,458 --> 00:21:20,292
Coming all this way yourself.

313
00:21:20,583 --> 00:21:21,708
Save it.

314
00:21:22,458 --> 00:21:24,042
Why did you run away?

315
00:21:24,167 --> 00:21:25,667
Do you have any idea

316
00:21:25,792 --> 00:21:28,417
what a mess our country is in
now that you've disappeared?

317
00:21:28,542 --> 00:21:29,917
But...

318
00:21:30,167 --> 00:21:31,917
How did you know I ran away to this place?

319
00:21:32,042 --> 00:21:34,792
I removed the listening
device from that little dog's ear.

320
00:21:38,917 --> 00:21:40,083
But...

321
00:21:40,208 --> 00:21:42,208
I didn't run away because I hate you.

322
00:21:42,875 --> 00:21:44,333
Is that so?

323
00:21:47,875 --> 00:21:49,542
But I hate you.

324
00:21:50,167 --> 00:21:51,917
You're not my type at all.

325
00:21:52,042 --> 00:21:53,250
Huh?

326
00:21:53,375 --> 00:21:55,375
I hate arranged marriages too.

327
00:21:56,292 --> 00:21:59,208
Then why did you come all the way here?

328
00:22:02,250 --> 00:22:04,083
If I bring you back,

329
00:22:04,208 --> 00:22:06,625
our engagement will be called off.

330
00:22:06,750 --> 00:22:09,208
Your father promised me himself.

331
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,250
Is it this guy?

332
00:22:13,750 --> 00:22:14,958
Is it him?

333
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:16,708
Your Highness?

334
00:22:17,917 --> 00:22:19,833
Wait, how can a princess be a guy?

335
00:22:19,958 --> 00:22:22,667
If you're handsome, you're a prince.

336
00:22:22,792 --> 00:22:24,184
If you're beautiful, you're a princess.

337
00:22:24,208 --> 00:22:26,000
Are you hitting on me right now?

338
00:22:26,125 --> 00:22:27,875
There are no women in space.

339
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:30,708
The concept of gender only exists on Earth.

340
00:22:32,875 --> 00:22:35,250
The way I see it...

341
00:22:37,792 --> 00:22:39,542
You must be a prince then, Your Highness.

342
00:22:40,417 --> 00:22:42,375
Hey, change of plans.

343
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,768
Let's stick around and have
some fun on Earth before we go.

344
00:22:44,792 --> 00:22:46,042
Why?

345
00:22:46,792 --> 00:22:48,333
How should I put this...

346
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:53,583
It's not easy to find love in space.

347
00:22:55,708 --> 00:22:57,000
Let's go.

348
00:23:57,375 --> 00:23:58,667
He's insane!

349
00:24:33,458 --> 00:24:35,208
Damn it.

350
00:24:41,958 --> 00:24:43,375
What are these guys talking about?

351
00:24:43,500 --> 00:24:44,333
Aliens?

352
00:24:44,458 --> 00:24:45,833
Wooju Bakery?

353
00:24:46,917 --> 00:24:48,292
You're all so dead!
